# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Spectra backend — CORS + in-memory vehicle state
# Load these into the process environment (e.g. platform secret/env UI, systemd, docker -e).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Comma-separated list of *browser* origins allowed for REST and CORS preflight.
# This must be your FRONTEND host (e.g. Vercel), NOT your Render API URL.
# No trailing slashes (match what the browser sends in the Origin header).
#
# Local (Vite default):
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:5173
#
# Vercel production + Render API example:
# CORS_ORIGINS=https://spectra-vehicle-os.vercel.app
#
# Optional: also allow every Vercel preview URL (regex; escape dots in host):
# CORS_ORIGIN_REGEX=https://.*\.vercel\.app
#
# Production custom domain:
# CORS_ORIGINS=https://app.example.com,https://www.example.com
#
# WebSockets: browsers do not run CORS preflight for WebSocket handshakes the same
# way as XHR/fetch. Starlette/FastAPI still validates Origin where applicable; keep
# frontend URLs listed above consistent with who may open `/ws/vehicle`.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Single-worker requirement (in-memory state)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vehicle state lives in process memory. If you run multiple Uvicorn/Gunicorn workers
# or horizontally scaled replicas without a shared store, each instance has its own
# state — REST updates and WebSocket broadcasts will not align across clients.
#
# For this project’s in-memory design: run exactly ONE worker per deployment unit,
#   uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
# (no --workers N with N>1 unless you replace the store with Redis/pub-sub, etc.)
